sentences: Mis te ometi teete! See on lausa barbaarsus.
context: The word 'teete' is the second-person plural present indicative form of the Estonian verb 'tegema', which means 'to make' or 'to do'. It is used when addressing multiple people and asking what they are currently doing. In context, it can also imply criticism of someone's actions, as shown in the dictionary example where it refers to barbaric behavior.
